p: \bThis particular Pokeball is ancient, and is unlike any we've ever seen!
\bCarbon dating places its creation at a time where there weren't any Pokeballs at all.
\bWe've dubbed it the "Ancient Ball", and we still haven't quite found its purpose.
\bI love exploring museums and learning about the past.
\bI would love to see a Kabutops before it became a fossil.\nOr an Aerodactyl!
\rWe measure the age of fossils through something called carbon dating.
\rBasically, certain elements will decay over time into other ones.

\bTo be able to see fossils and relics of so long ago...
\bIt's absolutely stunning. For an artist like me, it's the perfect inspiration!
\bI ordered these fossils from the gift shop, but they gave me more than I needed.
\bWhy don't you have one, instead? I don't need it.
